[{"source": "https://www.popsci.com/feed", "title": "The Marines used a \u2018robotic goat\u2019 to fire a rocket-propelled grenade", "description": "<figure class=\"Article-thumbnail orgnc-SingleImage orgnc-SingleImage--center orgnc-SingleImage--hasCaption\">\n                    <div class=\"orgnc-SingleImage-wrapper\"><img alt=\"The robotic goat with the M72 Light Anti-Tank Weapon on Sept. 9, 2023. \" class=\"orgnc-SingleImage-image webfeedsFeaturedVisual wp-post-image\" height=\"810\" src=\"https://www.popsci.com/uploads/2023/10/24/robotic-goat-rpg.jpg?auto=webp&amp;width=1440&amp;height=810\" style=\"display: block; margin: auto; margin-bottom: 5px;\" width=\"1440\" /></div><figcaption class=\"orgnc-SingleImage-caption\">The robotic goat with the M72 Light Anti-Tank Weapon on Sept. 9, 2023. <span class=\"orgnc-SingleImage-credit\">Justin J. Marty / US Marines</span></figcaption></figure><p>Here's why the US military put a light anti-tank weapon on the back of a robotic quadruped. </p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://www.popsci.com/technology/marines-robotic-goat-fires-weapon/\" rel=\"nofollow\">The Marines used a \u2018robotic goat\u2019 to fire a rocket-propell", "link": "https://www.popsci.com/technology/marines-robotic-goat-fires-weapon", "date_published": "2023-10-24T20:46:42+00:00", "bookmarked": false, "dead": null, "artist": "Popular Science", "album": "Popular Science", "user": null, "language": "en-US", "thumbnail": "https://www.popsci.com/uploads/2021/04/28/cropped-PSC3.png?auto=webp&width=32&height=32"}, {"source": "https://www.popsci.com/feed", "title": "Hurry and grab huge discounts on high-end soundbars during Amazon\u2019s pre-Black Friday flash sale", "description": "<figure class=\"Article-thumbnail orgnc-SingleImage orgnc-SingleImage--center orgnc-SingleImage--hasCaption\">\n                    <div class=\"orgnc-SingleImage-wrapper\"><img alt=\"A pattern made up of JBL subwoofers on a white background\" class=\"orgnc-SingleImage-image webfeeds