f=\"https://news.exeter.ac.uk/faculty-of-health-and-life-sciences/seaweed-eating-robot-listed-among-times-best-inventions/\">Seaweed Generation/University of Exeter</a></span></figcaption></figure><p>The AlgaRay scoops up invasive sargassum seaweed before it washes onto shores. It co", "link": "https://www.popsci.com/technology/algaray-seaweed-robot/", "date_published": "2023-10-24T18:00:00+00:00", "bookmarked": false, "dead": null, "artist": "Popular Science", "album": "Popular Science", "user": null, "language": "en-US", "thumbnail": "https://www.popsci.com/uploads/2021/04/28/cropped-PSC3.png?auto=webp&width=32&height=32"}, {"source": "https://www.popsci.com/feed", "title": "How kingfishers pull off breakneck dives without hurting their brains", "description": "<figure class=\"Article-thumbnail orgnc-SingleImage orgnc-SingleImage--center orgnc-SingleImage--hasCaption\">\n                    <div class=\"orgnc-SingleImage-wrapper\"><img alt=\"A kingfisher with blue and yellow feathers and outstretched wings dives through the air.\" class=\"orgnc-SingleImage-image webfeedsFeaturedVisual wp-post-image\" height=\"810\" src=\"https://www.popsci.com/uploads/2023/10/24/kingfisher-diving.png?auto=webp&amp;width=1440&amp;height=810\" style=\"display: block; margin: auto; margin-bottom: 5px;\" width=\"1440\" /></div><figcaption class=\"orgnc-SingleImage-caption\">Kingfishers can reach speeds of up to 25 miles per hour. <span class=\"orgnc-SingleImage-credit\"><a href=\"https://depositphotos.com/photo/common-european-kingfisher-dive-283706498.html\">Deposit Photos</a></span></figcaption></figure><p>Studying these bird brains can help scientists better understand traumatic brain injuries and even Alzheimer\u2019s disease.</p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://www.popsci.com/environmen", "link": "https://www.popsci.com/environment/kingfishers-plunge-dive-brains/", "date_published": "2023-10-24T17:00:00+00:00", "bookmarked": false, "dead": null, "artist": "Popular Science", "album": "Popular Science", "user": null, "language": "en-US", "thumbnail": "https://www.popsci.com/uploads/2021/04/28/cropped-PSC3.png?auto=webp&width=32&height=32"}, {"source": "https://www.popsci.com/feed", "title": "Rockets and satellites are shedding metal into the atmosphere", "description": "<figure class=\"Article-thumbnail orgnc-SingleImage orgnc-SingleImage--center orgnc-SingleImage--hasCaption\">\n                    <div class=\"orgnc-SingleImage-wrapper\"><img alt=\"Orang heat radiates from a reentering space capsule in NASA artwork.\" class=\"orgnc-SingleImage-image webfeedsFeaturedVisual wp-post-image\" height=\"810\" src=\"https://www.popsci.com/uploads/2023/10/23/Reentry.jpg?auto=webp&amp;width=1440&amp;height=810\" style=\"display: block; margin: auto; margin-bottom: 5px;\" width=\"1440\" /></div><figcaption class=\"orgnc-SingleImage-caption\">A space capsule enters Earth's atmosphere in this illustration. <span class=\"orgnc-SingleImage-credit\">NASA</span></figcaption></figure><p>This contamination could change how light bends or ice crystals grow.</p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://www.popsci.com/science/spacecraft-metal-stratosphere-pollution/\" rel=\"nofollow\">Rockets and satellites are shedding metal into the atmosphere</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://www.popsci.com\" rel=", "link": "https://www.popsci.com/science/spacecraft-metal-stratosphere-pollution/", "date_published": "2023-10-24T16:00:00+00:00", "bookmarked": false, "dead": null, "artist": "Popular Science", "album": "Popular Science", "user": null, "language": "en-US", "thumbnail": "https://www.popsci.com/uploads/2021/04/28/cropped-PSC3.png?auto=webp&width=32&height=32"}, {"source": "https://www.popsci.com/feed", "title": "Bumblebees carbo-load on the fly", "description": "<figure class=\"Article-thumbnail orgnc-SingleImage orgnc-SingleImage--center orgnc-SingleImage--hasCaption\">\n                    <div class=\"orgnc-SingleImage-wrapper\"><img alt=\"A fuzzy yellow and black bumblebee foraging on a green plant.\" class=\"orgnc-SingleImage-image webfeedsFeaturedVisual wp-post-image\" height=\"810\" src=\"https://www.popsci.com/uploads/2023/10/23/bumblebee-nectar-foraging.png?auto=webp&amp;width=1440&amp;height=810\" style=\"display: block; margin: auto; margin-bottom: 5px;\" width=\"1440\" /></div><figcaption class=\"orgnc-SingleImage-caption\">Bumblebees make decisions about nectar sources \u201con the fly.\u201d. <span class=\"orgnc-SingleImage-credit\"><a href=\"https://depositphotos.com/photo/bumble-bee-22895918.html\">Deposit Photos</a></span></figcaption></figure><p>They use their sesame seed-sized brains to prioritize getting the most calories as quickly as possible.</p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://www.popsci.com/environment/bumblebees-calories/\" rel=\"nofollow\">Bumblebees ca", "link": "https://www.popsci.com/environment/bumblebees-calories/", "date_published": "2023-10-24T15:00:00+00:00", "bookmarked": false, "dead": null, "artist": "Popular Science", "album": "Popular Science", "user": null, "language": "en-US", "thumbnail": "https://www.popsci.com/uploads/2021/04/28/cropped-PSC3.png?auto=webp&width=32&height=32"}, {"source": "https://www.popsci.com/feed", "title": "Chicken feather fibers could help make less toxic hydrogen fuel cells", "description": "<figure class=\"Article-thumbnail orgnc-SingleImage orgnc-SingleImage--center orgnc-SingleImage--hasCaption\">\n                    <div class=\"orgnc-SingleImage-wrapper\"><img alt=\"Chicken feathers are a major pollution byproduct in the poultry industry.\" class=\"orgnc-SingleImage-image webfeedsFeaturedVisual wp-post-image\" height=\"810\" src=\"https://www.popsci.com/uploads/2023/10/24/chicken-industry-keratin.jpg?auto=webp&amp;width=1440&amp;height=810\" style=\"display: block; margin: auto; margin-bottom: 5px;\" width=\"1440\" /></div><figcaption class=\"orgnc-SingleImage-caption\">Chicken feathers are a major pollution byproduct in the poultry industry. <span class=\"org